If respiration speeds up or reflex is present, increase isoflurane levels and halt the procedure until animal is fully anesthetized again.","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"7goua","text":"Place lacrilube ointment on eyes. Inject dexamethasone and buprenorphine.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"4ib36","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":[]},{"key":"17go5","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"notes","mutability":"","data":{"blocks":[{"data":[],"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"9evnq","text":"Giving dexamethasone pre- and post-operatively and maintaining sterility will prevent microglia from encapsulating the probe and reducing cell yield.","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"c978e","text":"Immobilize skull in earbars. Adjust nosecone AP and DV position as needed to ensure head is flat and centered. Set earbar on dominant hand side (at 5th tickmark), then hold neck scruff with dominant thumb and middle finger with pointer finger on the nose to manipulate the head. Position and secure earbar on nondominant side (at 5th tickmark). Tighten on both sides, then test by pressing down next to each ear. Confirm immobile and level before proceeding.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"9v3d1","text":"Sterilize scalp by passing iodine and ethanol with a cotton swabs alternately three times.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"bff7l","text":"Cut and remove the scalp from the skull. Lift the middle of the scalp well above the skull and make a small horizontal cut. Then, make small circular cuts around the first incision. The anterior boundary is a couple millimeters behind the eyes. The posterior boundary is where interparietal and occipital bones meet (suture behind lambda suture). Whenever possible, move skin away, rather than cutting. Hold remaining skin open with serrefines. Tighten earbars, which are often slightly loose following incision.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"baicu","text":"Clean skull with scalpel. Scrape away any connecting tissue and muscle connections to the back of the skull. Superficial bleeding will occur; clear with cotton swabs.  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":166,"length":1}],"data":[]},{"key":"25ek6","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"image","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"guid":"A86AAD0087B011EC93C2136B7B6ED224","height":403,"id":313235,"is_video":false,"legend":{"blocks":[{"data":[],"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"bj4fb","text":"Mouse immobilized in earbars, scalp shaved to eyes and ears, scalp excised to eyes and most posterior suture within shaved boundary, and skull scraped clear.","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":[]},"mime":"image/jpeg","nestedSelector":null,"original_name":"2.jpg","placeholder":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/jt6xbqrq7.jpg","shadow":false,"source":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/jt6vbqrq7.jpg","webp_placeholder":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/jt6wbqrq7.webp","webp_source":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/jt6ubqrq7.webp","width":550}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"fq527","text":"Find bregma, lambda, 2mm left and right of midpoint along midline suture with drill. Record changes in DV between these points. Level midline axis by adjusting nosecone DV, then repeat measurements. If using Neurostar system, use Adjust for tilt and scaling feature to adjust coordinates.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"a4vjk","text":"Make two marks to indicate the ML distance for the two MECs. Go to coordinates AP -3.9, ML +/-3.3. Bring the drill down to the surface of the skull and drill a superficial hole. Remove shavings with air duster, then fill holes with Sharpie.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"6t8m7","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":[]},{"key":"dmi58","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"notes","mutability":"IMMUTABLE","data":{"blocks":[{"data":[],"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"5nh3t","text":"This step is specific to MEC recordings. Adjust coordinates as needed for your target structure. You can choose to implant into left or right MEC in the next steps.","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"3355c","text":"Go to behind the sinus, midline (approx. coordinates AP -6.15, ML 0) to drill a hole over cerebellum for the reference screw.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"41vpc","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":[]},{"key":"arggg","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"notes","mutability":"IMMUTABLE","data":{"blocks":[{"data":[],"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"bu02v","text":"Referencing subtracts off the signal at the reference site. If analyzing LFP with an external reference, the reference screw needs to be somewhere electrically quiet, like cerebellum, so as not to introduce a new signal. If using an internal reference, this screw is just for grounding and thus can go anywhere. If not shorting reference and ground pads, add another screw anywhere on the skull and attach the wire from the ground pad (on the left, if the Sensapex holder is facing you during insertion) to that screw.","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"80dpt","text":"Score the skull with the scalpel to increase the surface area for metabond to bond to in later steps.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"9kq77","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"56gr5","text":"  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":[]},{"key":"84jgu","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"image","mutability":"","data":{"guid":"2AF8759087B111EC93C2136B7B6ED224","height":415,"id":313239,"is_video":false,"legend":{"blocks":[{"data":[],"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"aiccr","text":"Right and left MEC marked, reference screw hole drilled, and skull scored.","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":[]},"mime":"image/jpeg","nestedSelector":null,"original_name":"3.jpg","placeholder":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/jt63bqrq7.jpg","shadow":false,"source":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/jt6zbqrq7.jpg","webp_placeholder":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/jt62bqrq7.webp","webp_source":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/jt6ybqrq7.webp","width":419.57720588235276}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"vtoi","text":"Switch to cool light (e.g. from the scope) to better visualize the sinus. Using the air drill with the 0.5mm bit, shave down the skull in a ~1mm diameter circle behind (not including) your selected dot. Smooth down edges. Regularly stop to remove skull shavings with air duster and to clear and cool the area with saline to improve sinus visualization and to cool the brain to reduce swelling.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"qrsc","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":[]},{"key":"16rao","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"2mded","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"notes","mutability":"IMMUTABLE","data":{"blocks":[{"data":[],"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"2pj2g","text":"It is vital to visualize the sinus for good targeting, but not to drill into it, as this will cause severe bleeding. Once the sinus is visualize, shave down directly anterior to it to try to make the craniotomy as close to it as possible without including the sinus.","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"dtb28","text":"Once the skull is very thin above the craniotomy, use the fine-tip drill bit to carve a moat (approx. 0.5mm diameter) around the area that you will insert the probe (posterior to the dot, right in front of the sinus). You can test whether the skull is thin enough for this step by pressing gently on the skull with forceps and seeing how much it gives. If it’s rock-hard, keep shaving it down.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"54tsd","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":[]},{"key":"c4hkn","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"notes","mutability":"IMMUTABLE","data":{"blocks":[{"data":[],"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"70kg5","text":"Making a small craniotomy will reduce the amount of brain exposed post-operatively, but also reduces options for probe insertion.","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"3she8","text":"Once the moat has broken through the skull all the way around carefully lift the piece of skull off the brain using fine forceps. Some bleeding will probably occur when you lift off the piece of skull. Stop with Sugi spears. Use the fine-tip drill bit to smooth down edges, and use the bent forceps to look for hidden skull ledges to be removed. Try not to remove dura, and don't push the skull fragments towards the sinus.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"s6sa","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":[]},{"key":"aj0pn","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"notes","mutability":"IMMUTABLE","data":{"blocks":[{"data":[],"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"3kcoa","text":"If you rupture the sinus, severe bleeding will occur. Administer fluids and absorb with Sugi spears until a clot forms. Terminate the surgery, as it is you cannot use this craniotomy and it is unlikely you will be able to securely cover the clotted craniotomy to prevent future rupture under the implant.","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"dgaga","text":"When the craniotomy is clear and finished, mark the sinus with a Sharpie and extend the dot anteriorly with a Sharpie, to improve visualization once the well is added in next steps. Apply KwikCast to seal the craniotomy from glue in subsequent steps. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"1sbo9","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"bc368","text":"Affix screws in the drilled hole. Grasp with the bent forceps and place it on top of the hole. Use a screwdriver to slowly screw it in. Screw to the point where you can’t pull it out with your bent forceps (about 3 rotations; no need to screw it all the way into the skull).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"detro","text":"OPTIONAL: Attach the probe to the stereotax (see next section) and tax to just above the dot. Tax up, remove the probe holder, and store affixed in a clamp out of the way. When you insert the probe in the next section, tax posterior by 1.4mm to get to the target location (AP -5.1 for MEC).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"8tvqg","text":"Select a well size that will allow you to access the full craniotomy with an angled probe, visualize the sinus and center Sharpie marks, but not be too large. Apply a thin layer of UV cure glue, position around the craniotomy, and cure with UV light. This allows rapid curing so the well can be held in place and won't move around during gluing. Once secure, apply and cure a second layer around the outside of the well to make sure it can hold liquid.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"3vb7a","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":[]},{"key":"7jjjl","text":"  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":1,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":[]},{"key":"a1j0r","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"safety","mutability":"","data":{"blocks":[{"data":[],"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"46mnk","text":"Wear UV-filtering glasses when using the UV light.","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}},"1":{"type":"image","mutability":"","data":{"guid":"C24430A087B211EC93C2136B7B6ED224","height":375.07272727272755,"id":313243,"is_video":false,"legend":{"blocks":[{"data":[],"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"d097h","text":"Craniotomy surrounded by a well. Dot anterior to center of MEC (top) and sinus mark (middle left) are visible. Craniotomy sealed with Kwikcast (green) to protect UV glue (clear) from invading craniotomy while well was secured. Ground screw visible in bottom right.","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":[]},"mime":"image/jpeg","nestedSelector":null,"original_name":"4.jpg","placeholder":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/jt67bqrq7.jpg","shadow":false,"source":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/jt65bqrq7.jpg","webp_placeholder":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/jt66bqrq7.webp","webp_source":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/jt64bqrq7.webp","width":420.14256619144624}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"f7vtb","text":"Place headbar into holder and screw it in. Lower onto the skull. Position just behind the eyes. Center the marker line over the central suture. Lift up 1/2 turn.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"achv8","text":"  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":[]},{"key":"c5v4","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"image","mutability":"","data":{"guid":"0FAE753087B311EC93C2136B7B6ED224","height":495.8272727272728,"id":313247,"is_video":false,"legend":{"blocks":[{"data":[],"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"b9f85","text":"Positioning of skull components prior to metabonding. Headbar (top), skull screw (bottom), and craniotomy with well (bottom left).","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":[]},"mime":"image/jpeg","nestedSelector":null,"original_name":"5.jpg","placeholder":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/jt7bbqrq7.jpg","shadow":false,"source":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/jt69bqrq7.jpg","webp_placeholder":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/jt7abqrq7.webp","webp_source":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/jt68bqrq7.webp","width":422.7984496124032}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6d38e","text":"Prepare metabond in a mixing well that has been chilled to -20C. Add 1 scoop of metabond powder, 4 drops of solution, and 1 drop of catalyst. Mix well and apply with precision applicators. Let metabond run under the headbar, then lower it down 1/2 turn to put it back on the skull. Use metabond to cover the ground screw (including the soldering junction) and the entire skull. Make a bridge over the headbar with metabond. Apply a thin layer to allow it to cure completely quickly.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"acu2i","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":[]},{"key":"an7s","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"47v52","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"6n1rm","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"notes","mutability":"","data":{"blocks":[{"data":[],"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"ud6","text":"Metabond makes a strong connection to secure the headbar for headfixing and bonds well to bone, but is too runny to build up. Dental cement bonds well to metabond, but not bone, and can be used for construction. Covering the skull with metabond allows building atop with dental cement in future steps.","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"2hlp4","text":"Allow metabond to cure completely for   .","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":38,"length":1}],"data":[]},{"key":"ajvcm","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"6lqbo","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":1,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":[]},{"key":"dfjfq","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"duration","mutability":"","data":{"duration":600,"guid":"8398F23086C911ECBE06A55D2B5E7CC0","id":"81991","label":"","pause":null,"preset":[],"start":null}},"1":{"type":"notes","mutability":"IMMUTABLE","data":{"blocks":[{"data":[],"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"12hah","text":"Glues do not cure if wet. During gluing steps, constantly dry the margin (skin and muscle) and pull it away from the glued area with cotton swabs. While glue is curing, check the margins and pull off any excess glue so that none of the implant is attached to the skin, which can disrupt the implant when it is pulled during normal mouse behavior.","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"dmtp5","text":"While waiting: Mount rod to Sensapex holder, then to stereotactic arm. Angle the stereotax to 8-10 degrees (for MEC) and tax to just above the target location, either by eye or using coordinates from the earlier measurements from the dot.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"bl3oo","text":"While waiting: Remove rod from stereotax and affix probe. Slowly and carefully dip probe into IPA 3 times to sterilize, then DiD 10 times to dye. Store on a clamp out of the way.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"3hh0","text":"Release headbar from headbar holder and mouse from earbars. Mount headbar stereotactic adapters into earbar slots. Move nosecone anteriorly and ventrally until headbar is positioned snugly in headbar stereotactic adapters. Affix with headbar screws. Record nosecone position for explant surgery.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"3t83h","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":[]},{"key":"etfm7","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"notes","mutability":"IMMUTABLE","data":{"blocks":[{"data":[],"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"67hdl","text":"Moving to headbar mount means that the insertion angle can be replicated exactly during explant surgery.","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"b0ut1","text":"Remove Kwikcast and wash craniotomy with saline. Run bent forceps around the rim of the craniotomy to ensure no dried tissue covers the brain; if so, remove it.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"hk57","text":"Mount probe in Sensapex holder to stereotax with wings facing rostrally and lower to brain surface. Record DV start coordinate. Make sure entry is unimpeded, advancing 800um quickly (e.g. 0.5mm/s) to clear dura. If the probe bends, stop immediately and try a different insertion point.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"4jjb6","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":[]},{"key":"5v3aq","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"notes","mutability":"","data":{"blocks":[{"data":[],"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"d4s34","text":"If your target region is more anterior, you can flip the orientation so the wings are mounted to the back of the skull instead. Position the stereotax at a steep angle so you can visualize the probe through the middle slot of the body piece, watching to confirm that you don't hit the probe mount when positioning the scope. It is not recommended to rotate the probe 90 degrees (sites facing the ears instead of the nose/tail), as the probe will experience AP shearing forces during animal movement and the probe cannot bend in this direction.","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"2470f","text":"Drive probe at slowest speed (e.g. 3.3microns/s) to 3400 angled depth (for MEC), then retract 200 microns to ensure the probe will not hit skull when the brain settles. If the probe bends during insertion, retract until bend is relieved and either stop driving the probe or try another insertion. Driving to this depth takes 15 minutes.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"fma5n","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":[]},{"key":"eb0ih","text":"  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":1,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":[]},{"key":"c3r3d","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"notes","mutability":"","data":{"blocks":[{"data":[],"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"1m2l8","text":"Move scope to view the probe from the side. If the probe bends during insertion, it will bend along the axis visible from the side.","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}},"1":{"type":"image","mutability":"","data":{"guid":"53AC9DC087B311EC93C2136B7B6ED224","height":322.44,"id":313251,"is_video":false,"legend":{"blocks":[{"data":[],"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"25hka","text":"Probe at final depth inside craniotomy.","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":[]},"mime":"image/jpeg","nestedSelector":null,"original_name":"6.jpg","placeholder":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/jt7fbqrq7.jpg","shadow":false,"source":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/jt7dbqrq7.jpg","webp_placeholder":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/jt7ebqrq7.webp","webp_source":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/jt7cbqrq7.webp","width":413.3846153846153}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6krot","text":"Load blue \u0026 clear Dowsil components into 1.5mL Eppendorf tubes for easy access. Mix 20uL each of blue \u0026 clear Dowsil gels in a 0.5mL  Eppendorf tube. Draw up slowly as it is viscous. After mixing well, draw  up 20mL, and apply gently to the inside wall of the well. If it spills  out, wait to harden then scrape away.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}
